    • sellVechicle

      public java.lang.String sellVechicle​(int employee, int client, int vehicle, double paddDisc)
      sellVehicle sells a vehicle whose documents are up to date, applies the discount given. Post: the company's totalEarnings and salesAmount increase, the specific vehicle's owner is updated and that vehicle is removed from: all clients' interestedIn ArrayList of Vehicle, the company's fleet ArrayList of Vehicle (and oldParkingLot vehicle[][] if it was there). the vehicle is added to the company's sold ArrayList of Vehicle, the employee's sales increase, and the client is removed from the employee's assignedClients Client[].
      Parameters:
      employee - an int, must represent the position (index) of an employee in the CarDealer's employees Employee[]
      client - an int, must represent the position (index) of a Client in an employee's assignedClients Client[]
      vehicle - an int, must represent the position (index) of a Vehicle in the Client's interestedIn ArrayList of Vehicle
      paddDisc - a double, not negative
      Returns:
      a String saying the vehicle was sold successfully, at which price, who the new owner is and the updated sales and earnings of the CarDealer

    • sellVechicle

      public java.lang.String sellVechicle​(int employee, int client, int vehicle, double paddDisc, double price1, int year1, double paccidentCoverage, double price2, int year2, double pgasLevel)
      sellVehicle sells a vehicle whose documents are both expired or have to be generated, applies the discount given. Post: The vehicle's documents are renewed and assigned and that cost is added to the vehicle's totalPrice, the company's totalEarnings and salesAmount increase, the specific vehicle's owner is updated and that vehicle is removed from: all clients' interestedIn ArrayList of Vehicle, the company's fleet ArrayList of Vehicle (and oldParkingLot vehicle[][] if it was there). the vehicle is added to the company's sold ArrayList of Vehicle, the employee's sales increase, and the client is removed from the employee's assignedClients Client[].
      Parameters:
      employee - an int, must represent the position (index) of an employee in the CarDealer's employees Employee[]
      client - an int, must represent the position (index) of a Client in an employee's assignedClients Client[]
      vehicle - an int, must represent the position (index) of a Vehicle in the Client's interestedIn ArrayList of Vehicle
      paddDisc - a double, not negative
      price1 - a double, not negative
      year1 - an int, not negative
      paccidentCoverage - a double, not negative
      price2 - a double, not negative
      year2 - an int, not negative
      pgasLevel - a double, not negative
      Returns:
      a String saying the vehicle was sold successfully, at which price, who the new owner is and the updated sales and earnings of the CarDealer

    • sellVechicle

      public java.lang.String sellVechicle​(int employee, int client, int vehicle, double paddDisc, double pprice1, int pyear1, double paccidentCoverage, int ident)
      sellVehicle sells a vehicle with one expired document, applies the discount given. Post: The vehicle's expired document is renewed and assigned and that cost is added to the vehicle's totalPrice, the company's totalEarnings and salesAmount increase, the specific vehicle's owner is updated and that vehicle is removed from: all clients' interestedIn ArrayList of Vehicle, the company's fleet ArrayList of Vehicle (and oldParkingLot vehicle[][] if it was there). the vehicle is added to the company's sold ArrayList of Vehicle, the employee's sales increase, and the client is removed from the employee's assignedClients Client[].
      Parameters:
      employee - an int, must represent the position (index) of an employee in the CarDealer's employees Employee[]
      client - an int, must represent the position (index) of a Client in an employee's assignedClients Client[]
      vehicle - an int, must represent the position (index) of a Vehicle in the Client's interestedIn ArrayList of Vehicle
      paddDisc - a double, not negative
      pprice1 - a double, not negative
      pyear1 - an int, not negative
      paccidentCoverage - a double, not negative
      ident - an int, either 1 or 2
      Returns:
      a String saying the vehicle was sold successfully, at which price, who the new owner is and the updated sales and earnings of the CarDealer
